---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../../components/SiteHeader.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="What Type of Oil Is Best for My Car? | Fastlane Synthetics"
  description="A simple guide to choosing the right oil for your car, including viscosity, oil types, and how to narrow down the best fit."
>
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-white text-slate-900">
    <SiteHeader currentPath="/articles" />

    <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-slate-900">
      <div class="absolute inset-0">
        <img
          src="/amsoilbackgroundarticles.png"
          alt="AMSOIL oil guidance background"
          class="h-full w-full object-cover object-[center_55%] opacity-40"
        />
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-slate-950/65"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16 md:px-10 md:py-20">
        <div class="max-w-4xl">
          <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-cyan-300">
            Oil Guidance
          </p>

          <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-black leading-tight text-white md:text-6xl">
            What Type of Oil Is Best for My Car?
          </h1>

          <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-slate-200">
            If you’ve ever stood in front of a shelf of oil bottles and felt lost, you’re not alone.
            Labels, numbers, and big claims can make a simple choice feel more complicated than it needs to be.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-white">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-16 md:px-10">
        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-8 shadow-sm md:p-10">
          <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-[#005baa]">
            The short answer
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-slate-700">
            The best oil for your car is the one that matches your owner’s manual for viscosity,
            required specifications, and intended use. Once those are matched, choosing a quality
            product becomes much easier.
          </p>
        </div>

        <figure class="mt-10 overflow-hidden rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm">
          <img
            src="/article-first.png"
            alt="Comparison of 5W-20, 5W-30, and 10W-30 motor oil"
            class="h-full w-full object-cover"
          />
          <figcaption class="border-t border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 px-5 py-4 text-sm leading-6 text-slate-600">
            Choosing between 5W-20, 5W-30, and 10W-30 starts with your owner’s manual and the conditions you actually drive in.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <div class="mt-14 space-y-14">
          <section>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-slate-900">
              Why oil choice matters
            </h2>
            <div class="mt-5 space-y-5 text-lg leading-8 text-slate-700">
              <p>
                Engine oil does more than lubricate moving parts. It also helps manage heat, reduce
                wear, control deposits, and support cleaner engine operation over time.
              </p>
              <p>
                Modern engines are built around specific oil behaviour, especially during cold starts
                and at full operating temperature. That is why the right oil grade matters more than
                many drivers realize.
              </p>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-slate-900">
              What those numbers mean
            </h2>
            <div class="mt-5 space-y-5 text-lg leading-8 text-slate-700">
              <p>
                When you see something like 5W-30 on a bottle, the first part relates to how the oil
                behaves in colder conditions, while the second part relates to how it behaves once the
                engine is hot.
              </p>
              <p>
                In plain terms, your engine was designed around a certain viscosity range. The right
                oil needs to move properly on startup and still protect when the engine is fully warm.
              </p>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-slate-900">
              The main types of oil
            </h2>

            <div class="mt-6 grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-2">
              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-slate-900">Conventional oil</h3>
                <p class="mt-3 leading-8 text-slate-600">
                  Often suitable for some older vehicles if it meets the correct grade and specification.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-slate-900">Synthetic blend</h3>
                <p class="mt-3 leading-8 text-slate-600">
                  A middle-ground option that combines elements of conventional and synthetic oil.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-slate-900">Full synthetic</h3>
                <p class="mt-3 leading-8 text-slate-600">
                  Commonly chosen for better stability in heat and cold, along with stronger protection in demanding use.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">
                <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-slate-900">High-mileage oil</h3>
                <p class="mt-3 leading-8 text-slate-600">
                  Typically aimed at older engines and often focused on cleanliness and seal support.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-slate-900">
              So what is best for your car?
            </h2>
            <div class="mt-5 space-y-5 text-lg leading-8 text-slate-700">
              <p>
                Start with your owner’s manual, not the loudest bottle on the shelf. Look for the
                recommended viscosity, any required certifications, and whether your driving conditions
                call for anything specific.
              </p>
              <p>
                If you drive in very hot weather, tow regularly, have a turbocharged engine, or put
                your vehicle through harder use, product quality becomes even more important after you
                match the correct specification.
              </p>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section class="rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-8 shadow-sm md:p-10">
            <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-[#005baa]">
              Fastlane tip
            </p>
            <h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-black text-slate-900">
              Match the manual first, then choose quality
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-8 text-slate-700">
              The best choice usually is not about picking the most expensive bottle. It is about
              using the right viscosity, the right specification, and a product you can trust for how
              you actually drive.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-slate-900">
              Where AMSOIL and Fastlane Synthetics fit
            </h2>
            <div class="mt-5 space-y-5 text-lg leading-8 text-slate-700">
              <p>
                Once you know what your vehicle requires, the next step is choosing a product that
                matches those requirements with confidence. That is where better product guidance can
                make the process simpler.
              </p>
              <p>
                If you are unsure where to start, using a product guide or getting help narrowing down
                the right option can save time and help you avoid buying the wrong product.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row">
              <a
                href="/how-to-order"
                class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-[#005baa] px-8 py-4 text-base font-bold text-white transition hover:bg-[#004a8c]"
              >
                Find Product Help
              </a>

              <a
                href="https://www.amsoil.com/guides/?zo=5039461"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-[#ef1c25] px-8 py-4 text-base font-bold text-white transition hover:bg-[#d8151d]"
              >
                Use Product Guide
              </a>
            </div>
          </section>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-slate-950">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-slate-950/80"></div>

      <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 py-14 md:px-10 md:py-16">
        <div class="max-w-3xl">
          <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-cyan-300">
            Need Help Now?
          </p>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-white md:text-5xl">
            Want help choosing the right AMSOIL product?
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-5 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-8 text-slate-200">
            Reach out if you want help narrowing down the right AMSOIL product for your vehicle,
            motorcycle, or equipment.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row">
            <a
              href="/how-to-order"
              class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-[#ef1c25] px-8 py-4 text-base font-bold text-white transition hover:bg-[#d8151d]"
            >
              How to Order
            </a>

            <a
              href="/contact"
              class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl border border-white/20 px-8 py-4 text-base font-bold text-white transition hover:bg-white/10"
            >
              Contact Us
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
